<li><i>Healthy People 2000</i>, pp. 196-197.
<li>A brief but informative summary of adolescent developmental psychology as it relates to teen pregnancy has been written by Mary Beth Seader Style, M.S.W., Vice President for Policy and Practice at the National Committee for Adoption in Washington, D.C. This article, "The Developmental Stage of Adolescence," is available from the author upon request.
<li> Michael Males, "School Age Pregnancy:  Why Hasn't Prevention Worked?"  <i>Journal of School Health</i>, Vol. 63, No. 10 (December 1993), pp. 429-432.
